      • parser

        public void parser(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<java.lang.String>> m,
                   java.lang.String start)
        This function is the parser that goes thru the list by first getting the first set of reachable nodes from the very start. Essentially jump starting the loop afterwords. It will then make sure that what it will try to check isn't null and also that it isn't in the already checked nodes, otherwise it would probably end up with loops or redundant checks/info. If it has passed the if statements it will begin to gather all of the reachable's reachables, and add to the reachable list as it goes until it is finished.
        Parameters:
        m - this is the map of the edges
        start - this is the starting node
